  "scripts": {
    "dev": "vite"
    I found one issue immediately.

Your client/package.json only has:

"scripts": {
  "dev": "vite"
}

It is missing the build script, so Render cannot build your frontend.

Step 1: Update client/package.json

Replace the scripts section with:

"scripts": {
  "dev": "vite",
  "build": "vite build",
  "preview": "vite preview"
}

So your file should become:

{
  "name": "client",
  "private": true,
  "version": "1.0.0",
  "type": "module",
  "scripts": {
    "dev": "vite",
    "build": "vite build",
    "preview": "vite preview"
  },
  
  "dependencies": {
    "react": "^18.3.1",
    "react-dom": "^18.3.1"
  },
  "devDependencies": {
    "@vitejs/plugin-react": "^4.3.1",
    "autoprefixer": "^10.4.20",
    "postcss": "^8.4.49",
    "tailwindcss": "^3.4.16",
    "vite": "^5.4.10"
  }
}